
itools 0.60.4 (2009/09/08)
==========================

itools is a Python library, it groups a number of packages into a single
meta-package for easier development and deployment:

  itools.abnf             itools.ical             itools.stl
  itools.core             itools.odf              itools.tmx
  itools.csv              itools.office           itools.uri
  itools.datatypes        itools.pdf              itools.vfs
  itools.gettext          itools.pkg              itools.web
  itools.git              itools.python           itools.workflow
  itools.handlers         itools.relaxng          itools.xapian
  itools.html             itools.rest             itools.xliff
  itools.http             itools.rss              itools.xml
  itools.i18n             itools.srx              itools.xmlfile

The iodf-greek.py script, used to anonymize ODF documents, now tries to
preserve the text's width by replacing characters by other characters of
a similar width.  It also produces a nice thumbnail, in PNG and PDF
formats.

Support has been added to internationalize PML (PDF Markup Language)
templates.  Other improvements to PML include the new "<nobreak>"
element.

The list of languages (itools.i18n) has been updated to the latest
revision of the ISO 639-1 standard [1].  The language names have been
internationalized, and some have been translated.  The Chinese locale
has been added.

Several bugs have been fixed, including #685, #726, #735 and #746.


[1] http://www.loc.gov/standards/iso639-2/php/code_list.php


